      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (NIH/RH) directly maps to the clinical hemolysis endpoint; mapping documented.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the recognized regulatory surrogate for pump-induced hemolysis per FDA guidance. RH < 1 acceptance criterion directly reflects the clinical non-inferiority standard relative to the predicate device. QoI relevance is well established in the literature."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
