      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities cover the geometry, flow regime, and fluid properties representative of the COU; coverage documented.",
      "rationale": "Validation conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry at CPB-relevant flow rates (2.5–6 L/min) and speeds (2000–3500 RPM) using bovine blood at physiological hematocrit. Geometry and operating envelope are representative of the COU. Validation activities address nominal in-vitro conditions; the in vivo operational environment including prolonged duty cycles and hardware degradation over device lifetime is not reflected in the validation campaign, but this gap is not flagged as a credibility concern in the current assessment."
    },
    {
